.TH ICAL\-GUY 1 "2026-02-17" "ical-guy 0.10.2" "General Commands Manual"
.SH NAME
ical\-guy \- query macOS calendar events, reminders, and manage meetings
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ical\-guy
.RI [ subcommand ]
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ical\-guy
is a command\-line tool for querying macOS calendar events and reminders via
EventKit.
It supports text and JSON output, ANSI colors, meeting detection
(Zoom, Google Meet, Teams, WebEx), reminders, and TOML configuration.
It is designed as a modern replacement for icalBuddy.
.PP
When no subcommand is given,
.B events
is used by default.
.PP
Output format is auto\-detected: text when stdout is a terminal, JSON when
piped. Override with
.BR \-\-format .
.PP
Colors are enabled by default and adapt to terminal capabilities
(truecolor, 256\-color, 16\-color). Disable with
.B \-\-no\-color
or by setting the
.B NO_COLOR
environment variable.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B events
Query calendar events.
This is the default subcommand.
.TP
.B calendars
List available calendars.
.TP
.B meeting now
Show current meeting details with time remaining.
.TP
.B meeting next
Show next upcoming meeting with time until start.
.TP
.B meeting open
Open current meeting URL in a browser.
Supports per\-vendor browser selection via config or the
.B \-\-browser
flag.
Use
.B \-\-next
to open the next upcoming meeting instead.
.TP
.B meeting list
List today's meetings (events with detected video call URLs).
.TP
.B birthdays
List upcoming birthdays from the Contacts birthday calendar.
Defaults to the next 30 days.
.TP
.B reminders list
List reminders.
This is the default reminders subcommand.
Defaults to showing incomplete reminders.
.TP
.B reminders lists
List available reminder lists.
.TP
.B conflicts
Detect double\-booked events in a date range.
Excludes all\-day events by default.
Automatically filters out canceled events, free\-availability events,
and events the current user has declined.
.TP
.B free
Find free time slots within working hours for deep work planning.
Supports configurable working hours and minimum slot duration.
Uses the same scheduling filters as
.BR conflicts .
.TP
.B week
Print the Calendar.app week number for a given date.
Does not require EventKit access.
.TP
.B help
Show help information.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
These options are available on most subcommands.
.TP
.BI \-\-format " format"
Output format:
.B json
or
.BR text .
Auto\-detects based on whether stdout is a TTY if not specified.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable colored output.
.TP
.BI \-\-group\-by " mode"
Group output by the given mode.
Valid values:
.BR none " (flat list),"
.BR date " (group by date),"
.BR calendar " (group by calendar/list)."
For events, multi\-day ranges default to
.BR date ;
single\-day ranges default to
.BR none .
For reminders,
.B calendar
groups by reminder list.
.TP
.B \-\-show\-empty\-dates
Show dates with no events when grouping by date.
Implies
.BR "\-\-group\-by date" .
.TP
.BI \-\-time\-format " pattern"
Time format string (ICU pattern, e.g. "HH:mm" for 24\-hour).
Overrides the
.B [templates] time\-format
config value.
.TP
.BI \-\-date\-format " pattern"
Date format string (ICU pattern, e.g. "yyyy\-MM\-dd").
Overrides the
.B [templates] date\-format
config value.
.TP
.B \-\-show\-uid
Show event UIDs in text output.
.TP
.BI \-\-bullet " string"
Bullet prefix for each event (e.g. "\(->") ").
Overrides the
.B [templates] bullet
config value.
.TP
.BI \-\-separator " string"
Separator between events (e.g. "\-\-\-").
Overrides the
.B [templates] separator
config value.
.TP
.BI \-\-indent " string"
Indentation for detail lines (default: 4 spaces).
Overrides the
.B [templates] indent
config value.
.TP
.BI \-\-truncate\-notes " n"
Truncate notes to
.I n
characters (0 = no limit).
Overrides the
.B [templates] truncate\-notes
config value.
.TP
.BI \-\-truncate\-location " n"
Truncate location to
.I n
characters (0 = no limit).
Overrides the
.B [templates] truncate\-location
config value.
.SH EVENTS OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-from " date"
Start date for the query range.
Defaults to the start of today.
See
.B DATE FORMATS
below.
.TP
.BI \-\-to " date"
End date for the query range.
Defaults to the end of the start date.
See
.B DATE FORMATS
below.
.TP
.BI \-\-include\-calendars " calendars"
Only include events from these calendars.
Comma\-separated list of calendar titles.
.TP
.BI \-\-exclude\-calendars " calendars"
Exclude events from these calendars.
Comma\-separated list of calendar titles.
.TP
.BI \-\-include\-cal\-types " types"
Only include events from calendars of these types.
Comma\-separated list of types:
.BR local ", " calDAV ", " exchange ", " subscription ", " birthday ", " icloud .
The
.B icloud
type is a virtual alias that matches calDAV calendars with an iCloud source.
Type matching is case\-insensitive.
.TP
.BI \-\-exclude\-cal\-types " types"
Exclude events from calendars of these types.
Same values as
.BR \-\-include\-cal\-types .
.TP
.B \-\-exclude\-all\-day
Exclude all\-day events from the output.
.TP
.BI \-\-limit " n"
Maximum number of events to return.
.TP
.BI \-\-template " path"
Path to a .mustache template file for event rendering.
Overrides both
.B [templates] event\-file
and
.B [templates] event
from config.
See
.B TEMPLATES
below.
