.SH DATE FORMATS
The
.B \-\-from
and
.B \-\-to
options accept the following date formats:
.TP
.B today
Start of today.
.TP
.B tomorrow
Start of tomorrow.
.TP
.B yesterday
Start of yesterday.
.TP
.BI today+ N
.I N
days from today (e.g.,
.BR today+7 ).
.TP
.BI today\- N
.I N
days before today (e.g.,
.BR today\-3 ).
.TP
.B now
Current date and time.
.TP
.I YYYY\-MM\-DD
ISO 8601 date (e.g.,
.BR 2026\-03\-15 ).
.TP
.I "natural language"
English date phrases such as
.BR "june 10" ,
.BR "march 1, 2026" ,
.BR "june 10 at 6pm" ,
.BR "next friday" ,
or
.BR "tomorrow at noon" .
Uses macOS natural language date detection.
.SH OUTPUT
.SS Text Output (default for TTY)
Event display depends on the
.B \-\-group\-by
mode.
With
.BR date ,
events are grouped under bold date headers.
With
.BR calendar ,
events are grouped under colored calendar name headers.
With
.BR none ,
events are shown as a flat list without headers.
.PP
Each event shows time range, title, and calendar name.
Detail lines are indented below each event showing location, meeting URL,
attendees (as an indented list with RSVP status), and recurrence pattern.
.PP
When
.B \-\-show\-empty\-dates
is used, dates with no events display
"No events." under the date header.
.PP
Reminders with
.B "\-\-group\-by calendar"
are grouped under colored list name headers.
.SS JSON Output (default for pipes)
.B Events
.PP
The JSON structure depends on the
.B \-\-group\-by
mode:
.PP
With
.B \-\-group\-by none
(default for single\-day ranges), a JSON array of event objects.
.PP
With
.BR "\-\-group\-by date" ,
a JSON array of date group objects.
Each group has a
.B date
field (ISO 8601 date string) and an
.B events
array.
With
.BR \-\-show\-empty\-dates ,
dates with no events have an empty
.B events
array.
.PP
With
.BR "\-\-group\-by calendar" ,
a JSON array of calendar group objects.
Each group has a
.B calendar
object and an
.B events
array.
.PP
Reminders with
.B "\-\-group\-by calendar"
produce an array of list group objects.
Each group has a
.B list
object and a
.B reminders
array.
.PP
Each event object contains:
.TP
.B id
Unique event identifier.
.TP
.B title
Event title.
.TP
.B startDate
Event start as an ISO 8601 datetime string.
.TP
.B endDate
Event end as an ISO 8601 datetime string.
.TP
.B isAllDay
Boolean indicating whether the event is all\-day.
.TP
.B location
Event location, or null.
.TP
.B notes
Event notes, or null.
.TP
.B url
Event URL, or null.
.TP
.B meetingUrl
Detected meeting URL (Zoom, Google Meet, Teams, WebEx), or null.
.TP
.B meetingVendor
Detected meeting vendor ("meet", "zoom", "teams", "webex"), or null.
Used for per\-vendor browser selection.
.TP
.B calendar
Object with
.BR id ,
.BR title ,
.BR type ,
.BR source ,
and
.B color
fields.
.TP
.B attendees
Array of attendee objects, each with
.BR name ,
.BR email ,
.BR status ,
.BR role ,
and
.B isCurrentUser
fields.
.TP
.B organizer
Object with
.B name
and
.B email
fields, or null.
.TP
.B recurrence
Object with
.B isRecurring
(boolean) and
.B description
(string or null) fields.
.TP
.B status
Event status (e.g., "confirmed", "tentative", "canceled").
.TP
.B availability
Availability (e.g., "busy", "free", "tentative", "unavailable").
.TP
.B timeZone
Event time zone identifier, or null.
.TP
.B creationDate
Event creation date as ISO 8601, or null.
.TP
.B lastModifiedDate
Last modification date as ISO 8601, or null.
