Object with
.B from
and
.B to
fields (ISO 8601 datetimes).
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B ical\-guy
supports an optional TOML configuration file.
The file is loaded from
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/ical\-guy/config.toml
(defaults to
.IR ~/.config/ical\-guy/config.toml ).
CLI flags always take precedence over config values.
.PP
Example configuration:
.PP
.RS
.nf
[defaults]
format = "text"
exclude\-all\-day = false
include\-calendars = ["Work", "Personal"]
exclude\-calendars = ["US Holidays"]
include\-cal\-types = ["calDAV"]
exclude\-cal\-types = ["subscription"]
group\-by = "date"
show\-empty\-dates = true

[text]
show\-calendar = true
show\-location = true
show\-attendees = true
show\-meeting\-url = true
show\-notes = false
show\-uid = false

[free]
min\-duration = 30
work\-start = "09:00"
work\-end = "17:00"

[browsers]
default = "Safari"
meet = "Google Chrome"
zoom = "Safari"
teams = "Microsoft Edge"
webex = "Google Chrome"

[templates]
time\-format = "HH:mm"
date\-format = "yyyy\-MM\-dd"
event = "{{startTime}} \- {{title}}"
event\-file = "my\-template.mustache"
date\-header = "{{#bold}}=== {{formattedDate}} ==={{/bold}}"
date\-header\-file = "date\-header.mustache"
calendar\-header = "{{#calendarColor}}{{title}}{{/calendarColor}}"
calendar\-header\-file = "calendar\-header.mustache"
bullet = "\(-> "
indent = "  "
separator = "\-\-\-"
truncate\-notes = 80
truncate\-location = 40
.fi
.RE
.SS Browser Selection
The
.B [browsers]
section configures which browser application to use when opening meeting
URLs with
.BR "meeting open" .
.PP
Priority chain:
.B \-\-browser
CLI flag > vendor\-specific config key > config
.B default
key > system default browser.
.TP
.B default
Default browser for all meeting vendors.
.TP
.B meet
Browser for Google Meet URLs.
.TP
.B zoom
Browser for Zoom URLs.
.TP
.B teams
Browser for Microsoft Teams URLs.
.TP
.B webex
Browser for WebEx URLs.
.PP
Values can be application names (e.g. "Google Chrome", "Safari") or absolute
paths (e.g. "/Applications/Firefox.app").
Applications are searched in
.IR /Applications ,
.IR ~/Applications ,
and
.IR /System/Applications .
