.B {{displayString}}
Pre\-formatted display string (e.g. "John Doe <john@example.com> (accepted)").
Use triple\-stache
.B {{{displayString}}}
to avoid HTML escaping.
.SS Display Toggles
Controlled by config or CLI flags.
.TP
.B {{#showCalendar}}
Show calendar name (default: true).
.TP
.B {{#showLocation}}
Show location (default: true).
.TP
.B {{#showAttendees}}
Show attendees (default: true).
.TP
.B {{#showMeetingUrl}}
Show meeting URL (default: true).
.TP
.B {{#showNotes}}
Show notes (default: false).
.TP
.B {{#showUid}}
Show event UID (default: false, enable with
.BR \-\-show\-uid ).
.SS Decoration Variables
Configurable via
.B [templates]
config section or CLI flags.
Use triple\-stache
.BI {{{ var }}}
for decorations to avoid HTML escaping.
.TP
.B {{{bullet}}}
Bullet character (default: empty).
.TP
.B {{{indent}}}
Indentation string (default: 4 spaces).
.TP
.B {{{separator}}}
Separator between events (default: empty).
.SS Lambdas
ANSI formatting lambdas, disabled with
.BR \-\-no\-color .
.TP
.BI {{#bold}} text {{/bold}}
Make text bold.
.TP
.BI {{#dim}} text {{/dim}}
Make text dimmed/gray.
.TP
.BI {{#calendarColor}} text {{/calendarColor}}
Apply the calendar's color to text.
.SS Group Header Templates
.PP
Date headers:
.BR {{formattedDate}} ", " {{#bold}} .
.PP
Calendar headers:
.BR {{title}} ", " {{color}} ", " {{type}} ", " {{source}} ", "
.BR {{#bold}} ", " {{#calendarColor}} .
.SS Example Templates
Minimal (one\-line summary):
.PP
.RS
.nf
{{startTime}} {{title}}
.fi
.RE
.PP
Detailed:
.PP
.RS
.nf
{{#bold}}{{title}}{{/bold}} ({{startTime}} \- {{endTime}})
{{#hasLocation}}  Location: {{location}}{{/hasLocation}}
{{#hasAttendees}}  Attendees: {{#attendees}}{{name}} {{/attendees}}{{/hasAttendees}}
{{#isRecurring}}  Recurs: {{recurrence.description}}{{/isRecurring}}
.fi
.RE
.PP
With relative time:
.PP
.RS
.nf
{{#bold}}{{title}}{{/bold}} \(em {{relativeStart}}
{{#hasLocation}}  @ {{location}}{{/hasLocation}}
.fi
.RE
.SS Template Precedence
.PP
For event templates: CLI
.B \-\-template
flag > config
.B event\-file
> config
.B event
inline > built\-in default.
.PP
For header templates: config
.B date\-header\-file
>
.B date\-header
inline > built\-in default (same for
.BR calendar\-header ).
.PP
Template files are loaded from
.I ~/.config/ical\-guy/templates/
(relative paths) or from absolute paths.
.SH MEETING URL EXTRACTION
The
.B meetingUrl
field is automatically populated when a Google Meet, Zoom,
Microsoft Teams, or WebEx URL is found in an event's
.BR url ,
.BR location ,
or
.B notes
fields (checked in that priority order).
If no meeting URL is detected, the field is null.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
When set, disables all colored output.
See
.IR https://no\-color.org .
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for configuration files.
Defaults to
.IR ~/.config .
.TP
.B COLORTERM
Used to detect truecolor support.
Values of "truecolor" or "24bit" enable 24\-bit color.
.TP
.B TERM
Used to detect 256\-color support when
.B COLORTERM
is not set.
.SH EXAMPLES
Show today's events:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show events for the next 7 days:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy events \-\-from today \-\-to today+7
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show tomorrow's events from the Work calendar, excluding all\-day events:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy events \-\-from tomorrow \-\-to tomorrow \\
    \-\-include\-calendars Work \-\-exclude\-all\-day
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show only calDAV calendar events:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy events \-\-include\-cal\-types calDAV
.fi
.RE
.PP
Exclude birthday and subscription calendars:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy events \-\-exclude\-cal\-types birthday,subscription
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show only iCloud\-sourced calendar events:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy events \-\-include\-cal\-types icloud
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show the next 5 events in the next 30 days:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy events \-\-from today \-\-to today+30 \-\-limit 5
.fi
.RE
.PP
Force JSON output:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy events \-\-format json
.fi
.RE
.PP
List available calendars:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy calendars
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show current meeting:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy meeting now
.fi
.RE
.PP
Open current meeting in browser:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy meeting open
.fi
.RE
.PP
Open current meeting in Google Chrome:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy meeting open \-\-browser "Google Chrome"
.fi
.RE
.PP
List today's meetings:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy meeting list
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show upcoming birthdays:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy birthdays
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show birthdays in the next 90 days:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy birthdays \-\-from today \-\-to today+90
.fi
.RE
.PP
List incomplete reminders:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy reminders
.fi
.RE
.PP
List reminders due this week, sorted by priority:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ical\-guy reminders list \-\-from today \-\-to today+7 \-\-sort\-by priority
